#compdef rtlamr
# =============================================================================
# rtlamr — Douglas Hall's "RTL-SDR receiver for Itron ERT
#           compatible smart meters operating in the 900MHz
#           ISM band" — a Go-based Software-Defined Radio (SDR)
#           application that demodulates utility meter
#           Automatic Meter Reading (AMR) signals from generic
#           DVB-T USB dongles (RTL2832U-based).  Reads water,
#           gas, and electricity meter broadcasts that utility
#           companies use for drive-by meter reading.  Supports
#           multiple meter protocols:
#             - SCM (Standard Consumption Message) — most
#               common electricity + water meters
#             - SCM+ — extended SCM with additional data
#             - IDM (Interval Data Message) — periodic interval
#               readings
#             - NETIDM — IDM variant
#             - R900 — Neptune R900 water meters (915MHz)
#             - R900BCD — BCD-encoded R900 variant
#           Output formats: plain text (default), CSV, JSON, XML.
#           Used by:
#             - Energy researchers monitoring household usage
#             - Power monitoring enthusiasts logging consumption
#             - Security researchers studying utility-meter
#               privacy concerns (rtlamr can RECEIVE neighboring
#               household readings)
#             - Home automation integrations (rtlamr → MQTT →
#               Home Assistant for electricity dashboards)
#           Requires a separate `rtl_tcp` server providing the
#           SDR data stream (RTL-SDR USB dongle drivers).
#
# Author:  Douglas Hall (bemasher on GitHub) — RTL-SDR researcher
#          who reverse-engineered the ERT protocols + launched
#          rtlamr in 2015.  Continues active maintenance with
#          protocol additions for new meter types.
# Source:  https://github.com/bemasher/rtlamr
#          https://github.com/bemasher/rtlamr/blob/master/main.go
#          https://github.com/bemasher/rtlamr/blob/master/flags.go
# CLI:     main.go + flags.go — uses stdlib `flag` package
#          (already documented in taxonomy).  Headline
#          observability library: stdlib `log/slog` (Go 1.21+
#          official structured logging package) for all
#          diagnostic + error reporting throughout the receiver
#          pipeline + protocol decoders + rtl_tcp connection
#          management.
# Library: Go stdlib log/slog (Go 1.21+)
#          ("Structured Logging — Standard Library log/slog
#           package" — Jonathan Amsterdam + Go team — added
#           to Go's standard library in Go 1.21 (August 2023).
#           Inspired by structlog + zerolog + zap + slog-rs +
#           SLF4J — designed to be Go's CANONICAL structured
#           logger.  Provides:
#             - LEVELS: Debug/Info/Warn/Error
#             - STRUCTURED FIELDS via key-value variadic args
#             - HANDLERS: pluggable output backends (text,
#               JSON, custom)
#             - CONTEXT integration via slog.WithContext
#             - SOURCE-LOCATION capture via AddSource()
#             - GROUP/WITH for hierarchical field nesting
#           Shipped with EVERY Go installation since 1.21 —
#           competes with logrus+zap+zerolog for the position
#           that env_logger has in Rust: the "stdlib default"
#           that doesn't require third-party deps.)
# License: AGPL-3.0 (rtlamr); BSD-3-Clause (Go stdlib log/slog)
# Status:  rtlamr — 2468+ stars on bemasher/rtlamr; active
#          maintenance with periodic protocol updates;
#          Go stdlib log/slog — shipped with every Go release
#          since 1.21 (August 2023); rapidly displacing logrus
#          in NEW projects (existing projects keep logrus
#          because of installed-base inertia).
#
